// TEST: parse_tuple_index_diagnostic
// EXPECT: error E2092 at 18:5
//
// Tuple positional indexing `t.0` / `t.1` is deferred to v1.x
// (spec §7.6; changelog 20260513-0540-specs-changes.md). The lexer tokenizes
// `t.0` as `Ident`, `Dot`, `IntLiteral`, which previously fell through to the
// generic "expected expression, found `.`" parser error (E2020). The parser
// now recognises this shape and emits a specific, actionable diagnostic
// (E2092) that points users at destructuring instead.
//
// NOTE: the conformance harness parses directives but does not yet execute
// fixtures against the checker; the E2092 message and recovery behavior are
// asserted directly by the `bock-parser` unit tests `expr_tuple_index_*`.
// This fixture documents the expectation and guards the directive shape.

fn main() -> Int {
  let t = (1, 2)
  t.0
}
